reviewText: We've long been fans of MST3K, and had seen this "film" years ago, with the original MST3K commentary.  I didn't realize until we began to watch this version that it was a complete remake.  I assumed the "Cinematic Titanic" branding was some kind of collection-title, not an entirely different series.  The jokes are all new and the premise, delivery style, and characterization is totally different. So, watching this felt like calling an old friend only to find they'd had a brain-transplant.Sadly, the new "brain" isn't any kind of improvement.This remake just wasn't very funny.  Not in the way that the old series were.  Though the riffs are delivered by the original cast, they're oddly lifeless. No one's in character. They deliver the jokes in the manner of a kid forced to read aloud in front of his peers in history class. You know?  That dull, uninspired kind of reading where the words lose their meaning? In the original MST3K, the cast snickered up their sleeves, inviting us to join in the joke.  In this remake, the cast sound as if they're hoping we'll think their lines are funny, but they're not laughing. They don't even appear to get the jokes.  Not exactly an infectious energy.  Not at all like the enthusiastic satire that Joel (and Mike) and the Bots offered up with apparent spontaneity.  What happened, I wonder?Can't recommend these Cinematic Titanic remakes.  The original MST3K, however, is golden.

reviewText: Cinematic Titanic, Santa Claus Conquers The Martians, (#5)I'm thrilled to be the one who gets to offer the first rating on this movie!Some may not know, Cinematic Titanic is an off-shoot of MST3k or Mystery Science Theater 3000.This cast consists of Joel Hodgson (creator of both), Trace Beaulieu (a.k.a. 'Crow', J. Elvis Weinstein (who was 1st Tom Servo and created 'Cinematic's theme song) and Mary Jo Pehl. And you should know - that although MST3k did 'riff' this movie, Cinematic Titanic's riffing is all different on this one.The riffs (funny-comments between movie dialog) are suburb!! - The guys (and gal) don't miss a beat.I have watched it twice so far - and the 2nd time - I caught things I missed the first time.Amazing how unfazed the two kids are in this movie - about having been abducted my Martians.A great movie to riff on.  As noted - this is disc number 5 of the Cinematic releases(The Oozing Skull was the first one).One character in this is 'Droppo'(sp?) and he is not only 'lovable' he is irresistible for the gang to riff on.I saw Cinematic Titanic live in Concord NH, it was great!! And I loved the meet and greet after.Also check out their site for other titles, I think 7 so far.You can currently see the trailer of Cinematic Titanic's 'Santa Claus Conquers The Martians' on youtube (and other Cinematic titles).This movie is in color, and total running time is; 1:26:12I not only love this concept, I love this version of the movie!- And I think you will too!Scott MacNeil
summary: Cinematic Titanic, Santa Claus Conquers The Martians. #5
